text: Aïn Témouchent () is a province (wilaya) in northwestern Algeria, named after its capital: Aïn Témouchent. ==Administrative divisions== It is made up of 8 districts and 28 municipalities. The districts are: # Aïn Kihel # Aïn Larbaâ # Aïn Témouchent # Béni Saf # El Amria # El Malah # Hammam Bou Hadjar # Oulhassa Gheraba The municipalities are: # Aghlal # Aïn El Arbaa # Aïn Kihal # Aïn Témouchent # Aïn Tolba # Aoubellil # Beni Saf # Bou Zedjar # Chaabet El Ham # Chentouf # El Amria # El Emir Abdelkader # El Malah # El Messaid # Hammam Bouhadjar # Hassasna # Hassi El Ghella # Oued Berkeche # Oued Sabah # Ouled Boudjemaa # Ouled Kihal # Oulhaca El Gheraba # Sidi Ben Adda # Sidi Boumedienne # Sidi Ouriache # Sidi Safi # Tamzoura # Terga ==References== ==External links== * Official website Category:Provinces of Algeria
